{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/timezone\/new(identifier:)"]}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:4GLib8TimeZoneC3new10identifierACSgSPys4Int8VGSg_tFZ","roleHeading":"Type Method","title":"new(identifier:)","fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"new","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">?) -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib8TimeZoneC","text":"TimeZone","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone"]]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone\/new(identifier:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" corresponding to "},{"code":"identifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifier"},{"text":" cannot be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"parsed or loaded, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":" is returned.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"new","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"identifier","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">? = nil) -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib8TimeZoneC","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone","text":"TimeZone","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifier"},{"type":"text","text":" can either be an RFC3339\/ISO 8601 time offset or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"something that would pass as a valid value for the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TZ"},{"text":" environment","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"variable (including "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Windows, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifier"},{"text":" can also be the unlocalized name of a time","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"zone for standard time, for example “Pacific Standard Time”.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Valid RFC3339 time offsets are ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"Z\""},{"text":" (for UTC) or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"±hh:mm\""},{"type":"text","text":".  ISO 8601 additionally specifies"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"±hhmm\""},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"±hh\""},{"text":".  Offsets are","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time values to be added to Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) to get"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the local time.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In UNIX, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TZ"},{"text":" environment variable typically corresponds","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to the name of a file in the zoneinfo database, an absolute path to a file"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"somewhere else, or a string in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"“std offset [dst [offset],start[\/time],end[\/time]]” (POSIX) format.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"There  are  no spaces in the specification. The name of standard","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and daylight savings time zone must be three or more alphabetic","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"characters. Offsets are time values to be added to local time to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"get Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) and should be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"[±]hh[[:]mm[:ss]]\""},{"text":".  Dates are either","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"Jn\""},{"type":"text","text":" (Julian day with n between 1 and 365, leap"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"years not counted), ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"n\""},{"text":" (zero-based Julian day","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with n between 0 and 365) or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"Mm.w.d\""},{"type":"text","text":" (day d"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(0 <= d <= 6) of week w (1 <= w <= 5) of month m (1 <= m <= 12), day","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"0 is a Sunday).  Times are in local wall clock time, the default is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"02:00:00."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Windows, the “tzn[+|–]hh"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"#dzn"},{"type":"text","text":"” format is used, but also"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"accepts POSIX format.  The Windows format uses US rules for all time"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"zones; daylight savings time is 60 minutes behind the standard time","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with date and time of change taken from Pacific Standard Time."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Offsets are time values to be added to the local time to get","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Coordinated Universal Time (UTC)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_time_zone_new_local()"},{"type":"text","text":" calls this function with the value of the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"TZ","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" environment variable. This function itself is independent of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the value of "},{"code":"TZ","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", but if ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifier"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" then "},{"code":"\/etc\/localtime","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"will be consulted to discover the correct time zone on UNIX and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"registry will be consulted or "},{"code":"GetTimeZoneInformation()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be used","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to get the local time zone on Windows."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If intervals are not available, only time zone rules from "},{"code":"TZ","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"environment variable or other means, then they will be computed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from year 1900 to 2037.  If the maximum year for the rules is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"available and it is greater than 2037, then it will followed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"instead."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"See","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"http:\/\/tools.ietf.org\/html\/rfc3339#section-5.6"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for a precise definition of valid RFC3339 time offsets","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"time-offset"},{"type":"text","text":" expansion) and ISO 8601 for the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"full list of valid time offsets.  See","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"http:\/\/www.gnu.org\/s\/libc\/manual\/html_node\/TZ-Variable.html"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for an explanation of the possible","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"values of the "},{"code":"TZ","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" environment variable. See","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"http:\/\/msdn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/library\/ms912391%28v=winembedded.11%29.aspx"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for the list of time zones on Windows.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You should release the return value by calling ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_time_zone_unref()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"when you are done with it."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"#dzn":{"type":"link","title":":mm[:ss]","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":":mm[:ss]"}],"url":"#dzn","identifier":"#dzn"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"http://www.gnu.org/s/libc/manual/html_node/TZ-Variable.html":{"type":"link","title":"The GNU C Library manual","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The GNU C Library manual"}],"url":"http:\/\/www.gnu.org\/s\/libc\/manual\/html_node\/TZ-Variable.html","identifier":"http:\/\/www.gnu.org\/s\/libc\/manual\/html_node\/TZ-Variable.html"},"http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms912391%28v=winembedded.11%29.aspx":{"type":"link","title":"Microsoft Time Zone Index Values","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Microsoft Time Zone Index Values"}],"url":"http:\/\/msdn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/library\/ms912391%28v=winembedded.11%29.aspx","identifier":"http:\/\/msdn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/library\/ms912391%28v=winembedded.11%29.aspx"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/TimeZone/new(identifier:)":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone\/new(identifier:)","fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"new","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">?) -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib8TimeZoneC","text":"TimeZone","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/timezone\/new(identifier:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone"},{"text":" corresponding to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifier"},{"type":"text","text":". If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifier"},{"type":"text","text":" cannot be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"parsed or loaded, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" is returned."}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","title":"new(identifier:)","type":"topic"},"http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3339#section-5.6":{"title":"RFC3339 §5.6","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"RFC3339 §5.6"}],"url":"http:\/\/tools.ietf.org\/html\/rfc3339#section-5.6","identifier":"http:\/\/tools.ietf.org\/html\/rfc3339#section-5.6"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/TimeZone":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/timezone","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"TimeZone","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","title":"TimeZone","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TimeZone","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTimeZone"},{"text":" represents a time zone, at no particular point in time.","type":"text"}]}}}